ClassDecl.Name: GuiTab
ClassDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Represents a container with multiple named tabs.</summary> </Document>

ClassDecl.Name: ICommandExecutor
ClassDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>A command executor for the style controller to change the control state.</summary> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: ShowTab
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Select a tab page.</summary> <param name="index">The specified position for the tab page.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: SetCommandExecutor
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Called when the command executor is changed.</summary> <param name="value">The command executor.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: InsertTab
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Insert a tab header at the specified position.</summary> <param name="index">The specified position.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: SetTabText
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Set the text of a tab header at the specified position.</summary> <param name="index">The specified position.</param> <param name="value">The text.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: RemoveTab
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Remove the tab header at the specified position.</summary> <param name="index">The specified position.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: MoveTab
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Move a tab header from a position to another.</summary> <param name="oldIndex">The old position.</param> <param name="newIndex">The new position.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: SetSelectedTab
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Render a tab header at the specified position as selected.</summary> <param name="index">The specified position.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: SetTabAlt
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Set the Alt-combined shortcut key of a tab header at the specified position.</summary> <param name="index">The specified position.</param> <param name="value">The Alt-combined shortcut key.</param> <param name="host">The alt action host object.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: GetTabAltAction
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Get the associated <links><link cref="::vl::presentation::compositions::IGuiAltAction@s:vl.presentation.compositions.IGuiAltAction" /></links> object of a tab header at the specified position.</summary> <returns>The associated <links><link cref="::vl::presentation::compositions::IGuiAltAction@s:vl.presentation.compositions.IGuiAltAction" /></links> object.</returns> <param name="index">The specified position.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: GuiTab
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Create a control with a specified style controller.</summary> <param name="_styleController">The style controller.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: CreatePage
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Create a tag page at the specified index.</summary> <returns>The created page.</returns> <param name="index">The specified index. Set to -1 to insert at the last position.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: CreatePage
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Insert a tag page at the specified index.</summary> <returns>Returns true if this operation succeeded.</returns> <param name="page">The tab page to insert. This page should be a new page that has never been inserted to a <links><link cref="::vl::presentation::controls::GuiTab@s:vl.presentation.controls.GuiTab" /></links>.</param> <param name="index">The specified index. Set to -1 to insert at the last position.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: RemovePage
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Remove the tag page at the specified index.</summary> <returns>Returns true if this operation succeeded.</returns> <param name="page">The tab page to remove.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: MovePage
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Move a tag page at the specified index to a new position.</summary> <returns>Returns true if this operation succeeded.</returns> <param name="page">The tab page to move.</param> <param name="newIndex">The new position.</param> </Document>

FuncDecl.Name: SetSelectedPage
FuncDecl.Document: <Document> <summary>Set the selected page.</summary> <returns>Returns true if this operation succeeded.</returns> <param name="value">The selected page.</param> </Document>
